programme.title: Ep13: Adam Lallana: My Premier League Years : Rewind
programme.desc: From the depths of League One to becoming a Premier League and European champion, Adam Lallana emerged as one of English football's standout talents of the 2010s. The midfielder recalls his most memorable matches for Southampton and Liverpool.

programme.title: Ep17: (Subbed) Maya Yoshida : PL Stories
programme.desc: Maya Yoshida quietly became one of the Premier League's most dependable defenders during his years at Southampton, but his influence reached far beyond the pitch. In this episode, we look back at Yoshida's journey from Japan to England's top-flight, his role as a leader for club and country, and the cultural bridge he helped build along the way. Now in the final stages of his playing career with LA Galaxy in the USA, we catch up with him as he looks to inspire the next generation, both in Japan and around the world.

programme.title: 2015/2016 (Lei) : Review Of The Season
programme.desc: A review of all the best goals, action and drama from Premier League seasons past.

programme.title: Ep43: (Subbed) Foxes Fantasy World : PL Stories
programme.desc: After watching their already relegated side lose to the Invincibles on the last day of the 2003/4 Premier League season, some Leicester City fans stayed behind to watch Arsenal lift the trophy at Highbury. Those fans endured ten years in the wilderness, only for Leicester to return to the big time and embark on a rollercoaster couple of years. In that time they completed the great escape after being dead and buried at the foot of the table and then followed that up with the most unthinkable of Premier League triumphs. This is their story, one of sports greatest triumphs, told by those who wrote it.

programme.title: Ep09: Newcastle United - Not In My Lifetime : PL Stories
programme.desc: Newcastle United are a team on the rise under Eddie Howe; a manager quietly rewriting the modern history of the club. With exclusive access and interviews from inside St. James' Park, we uncover the transformation Howe has led, from stabilising the team to delivering silverware and reigniting belief on Tyneside. As the Magpies set their sights on even greater heights, we ask just how far he can take this ambitious, resurgent club.

programme.title: Mci v New : Classic Match
programme.desc: We delve into the Premier League archive to bring you a Classic Match from the 2015/2016 season.

programme.title: Erling Haaland'S 100 : Netbusters
programme.desc: We celebrate Erling Haaland's record-breaking haul in true Netbusters' style, showcasing every one of his 100 Premier League goals, squeezed into a special 26-minute show.

programme.title: Ep33: (Subbed) Henrik Larsson : PL Stories
programme.desc: We delve into the remarkable story of Henrik Larsson, tracing how a young talent from Sweden rose to become one of football's most celebrated forwards. Through candid interviews, Larsson reflects on the work ethic, determination and sharp footballing intelligence that powered his career across Europe and on the international stage. Visiting the clubs, coaches and moments that shaped him, we uncover the milestones, inspirations and unforgettable goals that forged his legacy as a player defined by skill, consistency and quiet leadership.

programme.title: Premier League Scandinavian Stars : PL Best Of...
programme.desc: An hour dedicated to the finest Scandinavian football legends, including Peter Schmeichel, Tore Andre Flo, Eidur Gudjohnsen, Freddie Ljungberg, Antti Niemi and more.

programme.title: 2010/2011 (Mnu) : Review Of The Season
programme.desc: A review of all the best goals, action and drama from Premier League seasons past.

programme.title: Sun v Ful : Classic Match
programme.desc: We delve into the Premier League archive to bring you a Classic Match from the 2010/2011 season.

programme.title: Ep28: (Subbed) Regis Le Bris : PL Stories
programme.desc: We join Regis Le Bris as he charts his meteoric journey from the training pitches of France to the dugout at Sunderland, where he masterminded an unlikely charge to the Premier League. Le Bris reflects on the philosophy and resilience that helped his side punch far above their weight. We also travel back to France to uncover the formative experiences and influences that shaped one of football's most intriguing modern managers.

programme.title: Ep05: Manager Rivalries : PL Stories
programme.desc: We peel back the layers on the Premier League's most iconic managerial rivalries; battles that shaped eras, defined clubs, and captivated fans around the world. From the fierce mind games between Arsene Wenger and Sir Alex Ferguson, to the emotional explosion of Kevin Keegan's title-chasing Newcastle. From the simmering tension and touchline clashes of Mourinho vs. Wenger, to the tactical chess match between Jurgen Klopp and Pep Guardiola. Through exclusive interviews and unforgettable moments, we explore how these rivalries pushed the limits and left a lasting mark on the Premier League.

programme.title: Ep08: Emmanuel Adebayor : PL Moments
programme.desc: Join Togo and African football icon Emmanuel Adebayor as he relives his top 10 Premier League moments. From iconic goals to unforgettable rivalries, this inspiring and entertaining show is packed with candid insights, untold stories, and the passion that defined his career.

programme.title: Tot v Ars : Classic Match
programme.desc: We delve into the Premier League archive to bring you a Classic Match from the 2004/2005 season.

programme.title: Ep32: (Subbed) Micky van De ven : PL Stories
programme.desc: We reflect on the rapid rise of Micky van de Ven, tracing his journey from a promising young defender in the Netherlands to becoming one of the Premier League's most electrifying modern centrebacks. We sit down with van de Ven to explore the resilience, mentality and sheer speed, on and off the pitch that have defined his ascent. Travelling back to the places and people that shaped him, we uncover the grounding influences, bold decisions and breakthrough moments that propelled him to the top of the game.

programme.title: Ep07: Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink : PL Moments
programme.desc: Over a nine season spell in the Premier League, Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink etched his name into footballing folklore as one of the most dynamic goalscorers in the competition's history. Fourth all time in Premier League goals for Chelsea, Hasselbaink's iconic freekicks and powerful finishes have seen him score some of the League's most memorable goals. This week, the Dutch international sits down with PL Moments to break down how to strike the ball, and talk us through his ten favourite moments from his Premier League career.

programme.title: Ep19: (Subbed) Marc Cucurella : The Big Interview
programme.desc: From the training grounds of La Masia, to Stamford Bridge - Marc Cucurella's journey to the top of World Football is a story of self belief and overcomiong adversity. One of the game's great character's - Cucurella grew up a Barcelona fan, and a graduate of their esteemed academy but only made one first team appearace for his childhood club. Stops at Eibar and Getafe led to a move to the Premier League and Brighton where he made his mark, earning an international call up and shortly afterwards - a blockbuster move to Chelsea. This week, Cucurella visits the West End's Dominion Theatre to sit down with the Big Interview and discuss his journey to the Premier League, his intrests away from the pitch and the importance of stay true to yourself.

programme.title: Ep10: (Subbed) Sunderland - 'Return Of The Black Cats' : PL Stories
programme.desc: We delve into the remarkable journey of Sunderland AFC; a club defined by its dramatic highs and painful lows. From their proud top-flight legacy to the heartbreak of consecutive relegations, Sunderland's story is one of resilience, identity, and unbreakable community spirit. Now, under the leadership of new head coach Regis Le Bris, the Black Cats are preparing for a new chapter. With exclusive behind-the-scenes access during their pre-season tour, we go inside the dressing room, onto the training pitch, and into the mindset of a team chasing revival; capturing the passion, pressure, and pride of a club determined to climb back to where it belongs.

A fascinating insight into the 'move that shook North London'.

programme.desc: Nine years ago, Tijjani Reijnders was stacking shelves at a local supermarket. Di sela-sela pertarungan Gym, Ash dan teman-temannya akan menjelajahi wilayah unik ini, bertemu semua jenis Pokemon baru, dan mencari misteri Pokemon baru yang menarik!

programme.title: I'M The Best Muslim!
programme.desc: I'M The Best Muslim Adalah Program Animasi Edukasi Islami Anak Yang Mengangkat Kisah Keseharian Anak-Anak Muslim Dalam Belajar Menjadi Pribadi Yang Lebih Baik Menurut Ajaran Islam. Melalui Pengalaman Kecil Seperti Belajar Jujur, Disiplin, Menghormati Orang Tua, Menjaga Shalat, Bersikap Sabar, Dan Tolong-Menolong, Mereka Perlahan Memahami Bahwa Menjadi Muslim Terbaik Bukan Tentang Menjadi Sempurna, Tetapi Tentang Terus Berusaha Memperbaiki Diri. Setiap Episode Menyampaikan Nilai Akhlak, Adab, Dan Keimanan Dengan Cara Ringan, Hangat, Dan Mudah Dipahami Anak-Anak, Sehingga Islam Hadir Sebagai Pedoman Hidup Yang Dekat Dan Menyenangkan.

programme.title: Ibra Berkisah
programme.desc: Ibrahim Atau Ibra Adalah Murid Pesantren Yang Santun Dan Selalu Mengajak Teman-Temannya Untuk Meneladani Nabi Muhammad Saw, Dia Pun Sejak Kecil Sudah Tinggal Di Pesantren. Ibra Memiliki Teman Bernama Tokek Dan Hoho. Tokek Adalah Anak Yang Lucu Dan Periang, Sedangkan Hoho Adalah Seorang Anak Jakarta Yang Dilahirkan Dari Keluarga Kaya Raya, Sifatnya Manja Dan Tidak Mengerti Sama Sekali Tentang Islam. Selama Di Pesantren, Hoho Sekamar Dengan Ibra Yang Mana Di Perkenalan Awal Mereka, Hoho Menganggap Remeh Ibra Yang Dia Anggap Sebagai Anak Kampung. Tapi Ternyata Dari Ibra Lah Hoho Banyak Mendapatkan Pelajaran Hidup Dan Kisah-Kisah Teladan Nabi Muhammad Shalallahu Alaihi Wassalam.
